===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|Balthasar}}, equivalent of the English biblical [[Belshazzar]]. From Hebrew [[בֵּלְשַׁאצַּר]] (''bēlšaṣṣar''), attested in the Tanakh and the Old Testament (Daniel, 5:1), from {{etyl|akk|en}} {{m|akk|𒂗𒈗𒌑𒀫|tr=bēl-šarra-uṣṣur|lit=May [[Bel]] protect the king}}.

